    <h3 id="secBraille">Braille</h3>
    <p>
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braille">Braille</a> is a system of raised dots used to allow non-sighted people to read by touch.  Each letter in the Braille alphabet is composed of a 2&times;3 grid of dots, some of which are "on" and some "off."  Any time your data can be subdivided evenly into a 2&times;3 grid, consider trying to treat it as Braille, especially if the instructions or flavortext use words like "touch" or "feel."
    </p>
    <img src="~/images/Braille.gif" />

    <h3 id="secSignalFlags">International Maritime Signal Flags</h3>
    <p>
        The system of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_maritime_signal_flags">international maritime signal flags</a> is a way of representing every letter and number of the alphabet in signals to or from ships.  They are defined by the International Code of Signals, or ICS.  Each flag features a simple pattern in a palette of five colors: red, white, blue, black, and yellow.
    </p>
    <img src="~/images/MaritimeSignalFlags.png" />

